  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nERC1538 is a very useful standard for transparent, upgradeable contracts that provides the following benefits:\r\n\r\n1. The ability to add, replace or remove multiple functions of a contract atomically (at the same time).\r\n2. Each time a function is added, replaced or removed, it is documented with events.\r\n3. Build trust over time by showing all changes made to a contract.\r\nUnlimited contract size.\r\n4. The ability to query information about functions currently supported by the contract.\r\n5. One contract address that provides all needed functionality and never needs to be replaced by another contract address.\r\n6. The ability for a contract to be upgradeable for a time, and then become immutable.\r\n7. Add trustless guarantees to a contract with \"unchangeable functions\".\r\n\r\n[See ERC1538 for more information.](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/1538)\r\n<!-- Is your feature request related to a specific problem? Is it just a crazy idea? Tell us about it! -->\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n<!-- Please describe your feature request in detail. -->\r\nIs anybody interested in adding an implementation of this standard to OpenZepplin?  I think it would be a valuable contribution.\r\n\r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\n",
